  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Operations Executive",
  "description": "<p><em>We are looking for a Senior Operations Executive to our office in Singapore, who can work independently as well as in a team.</em></p><p>As Senior Operations Executive, you will have an outgoing and driving role with a broad interface both within the company as well as with customers and suppliers. Your most important task will be to work with domestic\nand overseas clients including the global organization and provide excellent\nservice for all shipments assigned to you.</p><p><strong>The job:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage shipping documentation formalities</li><li>Ensure proper and timely billing / closing of all job files.</li><li>Coordinate day-to-day operations and transactions for freight forwarding and other related activities</li><li>Manage data entries in TMFF system</li><li>Coordinatewith various suppliers.</li><li>Provide Intercompany where relevant</li><li>Assist for rate sourcing with various carriers whenever necessary</li></ul><p><strong>Join us if you..</strong></p><ul><li>Have minimum 5 years’ experience in freight forwarding or Logistics Industry</li><li>Possess excellent communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>Pleasant personality and a good team player</li><li>Proficient in MS Office</li><li>Ability to work independently</li><li>DGR trained and OOG Cargo experience will be an advantage.</li></ul><p>To be successful you will have a proven track record and\ngenuine freight forwarding experience as this is essential to the role.</p><p><em><strong>Good reasons to join:</strong></em></p><p>You will be joining a leading company in the forwarding and\nlogistics industry with the clear ambition to further strengthen and expand our\nposition in the market. This newly created position gives you a great\nopportunity to help develop new clients from early stages of development.</p><p>We live and work according to our values, to get a bit\nbetter tomorrow than we are today. This is something that the whole company\nbreathes out. We work to promote a culture where \"<em>respect, integrity,\nentrepreneurship and fun</em>\" are part of our common everyday life, and\nexpand our DNA - but also the way we communicate with our customers and\ncolleagues.</p>",
